\begin_layout Standard
Warehousing is a solution to both of these problems.
 It provides a safe location where agricultural commodities can be aggregated
 and stored for longer periods.
 However, even when warehouses are available, farmers seem reluctant to
 bulk significant amounts of agricultural commodities and store for longer
 periods.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this paper, we focus mainly on the question: Why do farmers not store
 for longer periods?
\end_layout

